INSERT INTO courses VALUES(5,'Psy492','Consumer Psychology','PSY492: Consumer Psychology explores the psychology behind consumer behavior, covering decision-making, motivation, attitudes, and learning. You''ll dive into product development, marketing strategies, advertising, and promotional techniques to understand what drives consumer choices.');
INSERT INTO courses VALUES(7,'Psy405','Further Statistical Methods  in Psychology','PSY405: Further Statistical Methods in Psychology expands your toolkit with advanced stats methods, focusing on application over memorization. You''ll master SPSS, interpret results, and understand when to apply key statistical procedures in behavioral sciences.');
INSERT INTO courses VALUES(8,'Psy429','Perception','PSY429: Perception boosts psychological alertness, focusing on how we interpret and react to social phenomena. You''ll gain insights into individual differences, understand complex events, and find meaning in life. The course enhances understanding of how sensory info shapes behavior and relationships');
INSERT INTO courses VALUES(9,'Psy494','Motivation at The Work Place','PSY494: Motivation in the Workplace explores drivers of employee productivity, critical concepts, and key theories. You''ll examine goal setting, job design, and motivation''s impact on job satisfaction. Apply motivation theories to real-world workplace scenarios.');
